      "stages": [
        {"targets": ["sm_80", "ptx85"], "representation": "convergent ordered sparse m16n8k64 INT4 inline PTX with selectors 0 and 1", "stage": "backend_codegen", "mechanism": "inline_ptx", "outcome": "succeeded", "detail": "The 8,107-byte combined inline-PTX probe (SHA-256 ce31bb4c5d7f083ae8e1293a0a3e5196575482427a041d549f9ecd3862e46942) used public C, A, B, metadata, selector order and covered all eight variants with both selector values. Pinned LLVM emitted 8,453-byte PTX (SHA-256 7a8bb0261fd16c1941b47500d70f3cff95a1acb95c51e52480af15a4effc8818) with exactly 16 ordered m16n8k64 INT4 instructions. An auxiliary 6,948-byte typed LLVM comparison (SHA-256 379488c94c4e3d6b1806928d72723845b7bd329857f4dfc3caf8f74d7a5c6649) used source A, B, C, metadata, selector order and emitted 22,330-byte PTX (SHA-256 913b74cc0dba68779655073b83e5a534bcf076fa5e6a1d1d6029ef951b0fc1cd) with the same 16 forms; this record retained wrapping s4-by-s4 PTX."},
